President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of Vermont due to severe storms and flooding that occurred between June 25 and July 11, 2013. Federal aid will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. The counties of Caledonia, Chittenden, Orange, Orleans, Rutland, Washington, and Windsor are eligible for federal funding for emergency work and the repair or replacement of damaged facilities. Hazard mitigation measures statewide are also eligible for federal funding. Mark H. Landry has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments.